    "body": "I suppose if someone wants to silence a warning, that's their prerogative/fault, but we want everyone to at least have a chance to see them.  It's also _extremely important_ that all deprecation warnings be silencable by replacing code with something non-deprecated (otherwise use `PendingDeprecationWarning`, for which it totally makes sense to be off by default).\n\n> If your isympy users update IPython, they get warnings until you release a new version\n\nBut the other option (assuming we hadn't caught this now) would be no one notices that anything is wrong, until IPython releases a version that removes the deprecated feature, which completely breaks SymPy. The warnings way, folks bug us, and if the bug us enough, we'll be motivated to do a release.  But the breaking way, we have to do a bugfix release right away. \n"
  },
